<p>Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (TSMC) reported a 39.1% year-on-year increase in third-quarter net profit, reaching NT$452.3 billion ($14.76 billion), its highest on record and above market expectations. Analysts had projected around NT$417.7 billion, according to LSEG SmartEstimate data.</p>



<p>The world’s largest contract chipmaker, whose key clients include Nvidia and Apple, benefited from accelerating demand for semiconductors powering artificial intelligence applications, helping offset broader weakness in consumer electronics. [<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/china/tsmc-q3-profit-jumps-391-record-beats-expectations-2025-10-16/">Reuters</a>]</p>
