<p>China Changan Automobile Group and JD Group on Wednesday signed a strategic cooperation agreement in Beijing. Five major Changan brands, including Avita and Deep Blue Auto, joined the signing alongside JD Retail, JD Logistics, and other JD divisions. The partnership will focus on digital innovation across the supply chain, covering omnichannel marketing, smart logistics vehicle development, and overseas supply chain optimization. The two companies have previously collaborated on vehicle launches and upgrades to smart interaction centers. This new agreement aims to advance intelligent procurement and supply chain management, build a modular automotive logistics system, and support China’s automotive industry in its shift toward smart, low-carbon development. [<a href="https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/eBB70I2K4aMh43Nv06IsFQ">China Changan</a>, in Chinese]</p>
