<p>According to <em>South China Morning Post</em>, Apple is expanding its smart home manufacturing capabilities in Vietnam, entrusting Chinese company BYD with final assembly, testing, and packaging of its next-generation home devices. The new product lineup includes a HomePod-style smart display and a motorized tabletop robot.</p>



<p>The HomePod display is now slated for a spring 2026 launch, while the tabletop robot—featuring a 9-inch display on a movable arm—is targeted for around 2027. The devices will rely on LCD panels from Tianma, and despite the shift in production, they will still be subject to U.S. tariffs on imports from Vietnam. [<a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3329042/apple-taps-chinas-byd-build-homepod-screen-tabletop-robot-vietnam">South China Morning Post</a>]</p>
]]></content:encoded>
